It is often used in contexts such as anatomy, music, or geography.
model_response.example: The surgeon had to section the tendon to repair it. The students were sectioned into groups for the project. The park is sectioned off from the rest of the city. The company will section off a part of the building for the new department. The teacher asked the students to section their notes into different categories.

output_attributes: divide a single physical object into constituent parts
divide a set of elements into groups
isolate constituent parts of a non-physical object
cause to move or be apart
